# Git Workflow

## Branch model

- `main` — production; every push triggers a Netlify deploy. **Never commit or push to `main` without explicit user instruction.**
- `dev` — integration branch. All new development starts here or on a feature branch rooted in `dev`.
- Feature branches — branch from `dev`, e.g. `git checkout -b feat/my-feature dev`.

## GitHub remote

Remote is https://github.com/ur92/rsu_calc (public repo on personal GitHub account). Do **not** use https://github.jfrog.info/; that host does not have this repo.

## Rules

1. All new work must be based on `dev` (or a branch off `dev`), never directly off `main`.
2. Merge feature branches into `dev` first; then fast-forward `main` to `dev` only when the user explicitly asks to deploy/release.
3. Do **not** `git push origin main` or commit directly to `main` unless the user explicitly says so (e.g. "release", "deploy", "FF main", "push to main").
4. When creating a PR, target `dev` as the base branch, not `main`, unless deploying.
